{"content":"430:      * Signals whether a topic partition should be read by this log. Invoked on {@link #start() startup} once
431:      * for every partition found in the log's backing topic.
432:      * <p>This method can be overridden by subclasses when only a subset of the assigned partitions
433:      * should be read into memory. By default, all partitions are read.
434:      * @param topicPartition A topic partition which could be read by this log.
435:      * @return true if the partition should be read by this log, false if its contents should be ignored.
436:      */
437:     protected boolean readPartition(TopicPartition topicPartition) {
438:         return true;
439:     }
